Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Temporary 1.0 FTE Teacher Librarian Gold River , BC Description VANCOUVER ISLAND WESTSchool District 84TEACHER POSTING No. 2024-15 REPOSTEDTEMPORARY 1.0 FTE TEACHER LIBRARIAN REQUIRED GOLD RIVER WORKSITE – GRSS/RWES Effective September 1, 2024 to January 4, 2025 or return of the incumbent __________________________________________________________________________ Teaching assignment may include, but may not be limited to: Teacher Librarian for Kindergarten to Grade 12 The successful candidate will: have an exemplary work ethic, effective communication skills and a proven ability to work as an effective team member to ensure success in this setting; be committed to being an advocate for students; possess outstanding skills in building student rapport; provide a significant collaborative leadership role; model and support the development of 21st century literacies (including digital and information); provide coaching and mentoring for wise and effective instructional and assessment practices; develop, evaluate and expand innovative District resources and online Destiny library system be able and willing to work in a technologically rich education environment; use research based reading and writing instructional and assessment strategies; incorporate technology information literacy skills into the library program; select and obtain resources, both print and electronic, onsite and remote access; be familiar with copyright and site licensing; be willing to display a high level of communication, flexibility and collaboration; strong skills as a problem solver; strong skills in conflict resolution; deal meaningfully with differentiated student learning styles and demonstrate an ability to address individual student needs; provide a hands-on, active classroom experience for student learning, including the use of distributed learning; commit to supporting the school’s goal to improve student literacy, and be familiar with and knowledgeable about current Literacy practices, including reading intervention strategies, assessment and evaluation techniques, best practices, and curriculum surrounding literacy; commit to the District’s and school’s goals to improve the success of First Nations students; communicate with parents and guardians; be willing and flexible to teach other subjects; be willing and able to travel throughout the District, when required; be physically capable to perform the duties of this position. Essential Qualifications: BC Certified and qualified with a Master’s Degree/Diploma in Teacher-Librarianship;Valid Class 5 BC driver’s license. Successful experience in supporting individual student learning in a multi-grade classroom. Inquiries can be directed to the Principal of Gold River Secondary School – sbroderick@viw.sd84.bc.ca 250-283-2538, Ray Watkins Elementary School- ntoth@viw.sd84.bc.ca or at 250‑283‑2220. Interested applicants are required to submit their application by September 12, 2024 at 10:00 AM as follows:Current SD84 Certified Teachers may apply via this link: Temporary Teacher LibrarianThe District will only be accepting applications via the above links. Emailed and/or paper copy applications will not be accepted. If you require any assistance with your application, please contact hr@viw.sd84.bc.ca Compensation $61,488-$109,520 Closes: 12 December, 2024 Vancouver Island West (School District 84) Gold River , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
