Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Branch Head Librarian II - West Kelowna Kelowna , BC Description Career Opportunity Branch Head Librarian II – West Kelowna Okanagan Regional LibraryPermanent Full-Time The Okanagan Regional Library (ORL) is seeking an experienced, passionate, visionary, and community-minded librarian to lead the two facilities that service growing communities in the City of West Kelowna, Regional District of the Central Okanagan, and the West Bank First Nation. The Westbank Branch Head Librarian II is a key leadership position responsible for two locations, with a total staff of 13 people. This position is responsible for the Westbank Library, which is a centrally located traditional city library beloved by the community, and The Westside Learning Lab, an innovative library space focused on teaching and learning. The WLL includes the first Makerspace opened by the ORL, abundant flexible meeting and community space, a small collection and holds pick-ups. All leadership librarians in ORL also work collectively to provide strategic direction and assist with project work in support of the entire library system. The successful candidate will bring with them proven experience in developing and maintaining partnerships using a community led libraries approach. The individual will be planning and organizing library branch resources and services to meet the community needs and interests.They will develop and maintain effective relationships with staff, be a team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills, and stay current with trends, technologies, and best practices in public library services. Qualifications include: Master’s degree in, Library and Information Science from an accredited library school.Three year’s relevant public library experience including one year in a supervisory position. This position is permanent full-time 35 hours weekly. Salary range is $90,154 to $96,549 per year. Please visit out website at http://www.orl.bc.ca/careers/current-vacancies for the job description.Please forward a covering letter, a resume, and reference via e-mail to: jobs@orl.bc.ca. We thank all applicants for their interest in our organization; however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted. Competition Number: 24-102 Compensation $90,154 - $96,549. per year Closes: 15 September, 2024 Okanagan Regional Library Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
